3.01	Raskolnik	Raskol	Raskol (Russian: , Russian pronunciation: , meaning "split" or "schism") was the event of splitting of the Russian Orthodox Church into an official church and the Old Believers movement in mid-17th century, triggered by the reforms of Patriarch Nikon in 1653, aiming to establish uniformity between the Greek and Russian church practices.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Nikita_Pustosviat._Dispute_on_the_Confession_of_Faith.jpg/300px-Nikita_Pustosviat._Dispute_on_the_Confession_of_Faith.jpg
